## Import

> **Bulk import tip:** [`tools/generate_import/generate_import.py`](https://github.com/pescobar/terraform-provider-slurm/blob/master/tools/generate_import/generate_import.py)
> queries a running `slurmrestd` instance and generates ready-to-use HCL files plus
> `import {}` blocks for all QOS, accounts, and users in one shot. See its
> [README](https://github.com/pescobar/terraform-provider-slurm/blob/master/tools/generate_import/README.md)
> for usage.

Import a QOS by its Slurm name:

```bash
tofu import slurm_qos.standard standard
```

`slurm_qos` uses **Optional+Computed** fields, so after import the provider reads
all values from Slurm and state is immediately correct — no reconcile apply is
needed.

### Warning: built-in `normal` QOS

Slurm auto-creates a QOS named `normal` at database initialisation. You can manage
its attributes via this provider, but you **must not** run `tofu destroy` on it —
deleting it via the REST API corrupts slurmdbd. To stop managing it without
deleting it:

```bash
tofu state rm slurm_qos.normal
```
